data.description: 5.27 ACRES IN BROOKS AREA. Quiet dead end street inside Brooks City limits. Secluded 6BR “green” house, 4.5 baths, circle driveway. Front yard is open with grass, ready for fencing, barn, animals, or extra large garden; with sprinkler system. Home has Geothermal heating and air, which saves on energy costs. Beautiful southern charmed extra large front porch 80x14.  Two Master bedrooms on the main floor. Living room opens to pool entertainment area. Large kitchen with granite counter tops, hand made copper deep sinks (main and prep), custom cabinets, eat-in kitchen area with bay window over looking pool area. Mud room. Laundry room on main next to master bedroom #1. Formal dining room. Library/grand piano room. 4 bedrooms on 2nd floor are set up as 2 Jack and Jill’s. 2nd floor laundry area. Off of the bedrooms are two large common areas, one on each side of the house, perfect for a home office, school room, an extra bedroom, or an entertainment/TV room. Large, walk-in attic space. 2 car + garage with extra high ceiling to allow for RV parking. 5 yo Gunite pebble tech salt water pool with zero entry, hot tub with water fall. Outdoor entertainment area is an extension of the living room and kitchen, complete with propane for an outdoor kitchen. Roof is less than 10y old.
data.whatILove: I love that our home is spacious enough so that everyone can be doing their own thing without being on top of each other yet maintaining that sense of  community. The set up of this home gives you the privacy you desire, yet the ability to have a community with the 9 homes of friendly neighbors. Just a mile or two from downtown Brooks, the ball park, library, hair salon, post office, and shopping are easy access. Country living with easy city access.
